Chelsea manager, Frank Lampard has released his starting XI against Everton in today’s Premier League clash at Goodison Park. According to Football London, Lampard maintained the same team that started against Aston Villa in midweek. Below is Chelsea’s starting XI against Everton: Chelsea: Kepa; Reece James, Kurt Zouma, Andreas Christensen, Cesar Azpilicueta; N’Golo Kante, Mateo Kovacic; Mason Mount; Willian, Tammy Abraham, Christian Pulisic. Substitutes: Willy Caballero, Fikayo Tomori, Emerson Palmieri, Jorginho, Ross Barkley, Callum Hudson-Odoi, Michy Batshuayi. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.